#Text=Beranton Whisenant
#Text=Beranton Whisenant Jr. ( c. 1979 - May 24 , 2017 ) was an American federal prosecutor .
#Text=Early life and career
#Text=Whisenant graduated from the University of Florida Law School in 2004 .
#Text=He also studied shortly at the University of Cape Town .
#Text=He was admitted to the Florida Bar in 2004 and remained an active member .
#Text=For nine years he worked at a private law firm , Foley & Mansfield Partner , in Miami .
#Text=At Foley & Mansfield Partner he worked on cases of civil litigation , product liability , contracts , personal injury , wrongful death , and medical malpractice defense .
#Text=His next job was as Assistant State Attorney in Jacksonville , Florida , his hometown .
#Text=He joined the United States Attorney 's Office in Miami in January 2017 .
#Text=He lived in Miramar , Florida a suburb of Miami .

#Text=He was an active member of the Eleventh Judicial Circuit Professionalism Panel and Chair of The Florida Bar ’s Eleventh Judicial Circuit Grievance Committee in Division ‘ L. He was a member of the William Reece Smith Jr. Leadership Academy as well as a member of The Florida Bar ’s Judicial Nominations Procedure committee and of the Florida Supreme Court ’s Commission on Professionalism .
#Text=He was a guest teacher at the University of Miami Paralegal Program and the University of Miami School of Law and Florida Coastal School of Law .
#Text=Whisenant volunteered at Habitat for Humanity and volunteered as a lawyer , for pro bono legal work . [ 1 ]
#Text=U.S. Attorney
#Text=Beranton Whisenant worked in the U.S. Attorney 's Office in Miami in its major crimes unit .
#Text=The office prosecutes criminal and civil cases from Fort Pierce to Key West .
#Text=He was reportedly working on visa and passport fraud cases prior to his death .
#Text=Death
#Text=The body of Beranton Whisenant was found on a Florida beach with possible head trauma or possible head gunshot wound on May 25 , 2017 .
#Text=Miranda Grossman , a Hollywood police spokeswoman , reported that his body was found at 6:30 am , by a passerby on the city 's beach .
#Text=He was wearing a dress shirt and black pants .
#Text=Hollywood police detectives working to determine if the death was a homicide , suicide or something else .
#Text=All of Whisenant personal effects were on his body , so robbery is not a motive .
#Text=Whisenant was 37 years old .
#Text=He had been a U.S. Attorney for only five months .
#Text=His memorial service was held on June 1 , 2017 at Antioch Missionary Baptist Church in Miami . [ 2 ] [ 3 ] [ 4 ] [ 5 ]
#Text=Whisenant was survived by his three children , his wife , Ebony , a doctor who teaches at Florida International University ’ s medical school , and his parents , both Jacksonville physicians .

#Text=The U.S. attorney ’s office and the Federal Bureau of Investigation ( FBI ) determined that his death had no connection to his employment as a prosecutor or his federal criminal cases , leaving the death investigation to the Hollywood Police Department .
#Text=Hollywood police and the Broward medical examiner ’s office declined numerous public records requests on Whisenant ’s death . [ 6 ]
#Text=The lack of information from authorities about his death opened the door for hypotheses . [ 7 ] [ 8 ]
